                            <comment id="12668922" author="euphoria" created="Fri, 30 Jan 2009 16:51:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;pkg-config is listed as a dependency in &lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.apache.org/thrift/ThriftRequirements&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://wiki.apache.org/thrift/ThriftRequirements&lt;/a&gt; and in the various installation pages on the wiki.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is the README file the location that you are looking, in which it is missing?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12668926" author="gstein" created="Fri, 30 Jan 2009 17:02:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yup. The README. You know... the file that I downloaded onto my box, then consulted in order to get the build going? &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So... sounds more like this issue should be &quot;README should be updated to reflect the true set of requirements/dependencies.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12683721" author="bryanduxbury" created="Fri, 20 Mar 2009 02:27:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Does someone want to step up and resolve this issue so we can move on towards our release?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12683769" author="dreiss" created="Fri, 20 Mar 2009 06:51:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll put it in the readme.  pkg.m4 will not be necessary to build release tarballs since we&apos;ll include the pre-generated configure script.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
